### FINDINGS
[F-003-01] Peck adds an auditable per-finding block cutoff: every finding gets a numeric score and `Score >=4 blocks the PR`, while spec-kit blocks by categorical verdict (`P0` => FAIL, `P1` => CONDITIONAL, `P2` => PASS advisory). Peck: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/code-reviewer.md:68`, `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/code-reviewer.md:132`; spec-kit: `.opencode/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:333`, `.opencode/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:345`, `.opencode/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:347`, `.opencode/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:365`. GAP: partial. Spec-kit already has deterministic gating, but lacks numeric per-finding calibration. VERDICT ADAPT. EFFORT M. RISK med. BLAST-RADIUS: sk-code-review output schema + deep-review reducer/report schema only.

[F-003-02] Peck’s weights are mostly a P0/P1/P2 calibration table in disguise: 8-10 maps to spec-kit P0 security/correctness/concurrency blockers, 5-7 maps mostly P1 degraded behavior/test false-confidence/type-risk/architecture risk, and 4 maps P2-or-P1 context-dependent maintainability. Peck: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/code-reviewer.md:70`, `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/code-reviewer.md:87`, `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/code-reviewer.md:94`; spec-kit: `.opencode/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:337`, `.opencode/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:338`, `.opencode/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:339`. GAP: partial. VERDICT ADAPT. EFFORT S. RISK low. BLAST-RADIUS: documentation/rubric guidance, not core verdict semantics.

[F-003-03] Peck’s `±2 for context` is the most useful delta because it formalizes downgrade/upgrade discretion; spec-kit requires evidence, assumptions, adversarial replay for P0, and exact severity coverage, but does not give reviewers a bounded adjustment rule. Peck: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/code-reviewer.md:68`; spec-kit: `.opencode/skills/sk-code-review/SKILL.md:370`, `.opencode/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:382`, `.opencode/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:383`, `.opencode/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:451`, `.opencode/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:452`. GAP: real. VERDICT ADAPT. EFFORT M. RISK med. BLAST-RADIUS: reviewer prompt contracts and validation examples.

[F-003-04] Peck over-blocks maintainability if adopted literally: dead code, small duplication, unnecessary abstraction, and removable code all score 4 and therefore fail PRs, while spec-kit treats P2 as non-blocking advisory and reserves hard FAIL for P0. Peck: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/code-reviewer.md:82`, `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/code-reviewer.md:83`, `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/code-reviewer.md:84`, `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/code-reviewer.md:85`; spec-kit: `.opencode/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:339`, `.opencode/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:345`, `.opencode/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:365`. GAP: none for blocking; peck is stricter/cosmetic here. VERDICT SKIP literal cutoff. EFFORT S. RISK high. BLAST-RADIUS: would increase false-positive REQUEST_CHANGES/FAIL.

[F-003-05] Spec-kit already has numeric weighting at loop convergence level, not per finding: deep-review is “severity-weighted findings” with sibling threshold semantics, and final reports require P0/P1/P2 counts, but individual findings remain categorical. Peck: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/code-reviewer.md:103`; spec-kit: `.opencode/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:14`, `.opencode/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:21`, `.opencode/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:460`, `.opencode/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:461`. GAP: real but narrow. VERDICT ADAPT optional numeric `riskScore`, not mandatory gate. EFFORT M. RISK med. BLAST-RADIUS: deep-review JSONL/report schema if persisted.

[F-003-06] Spec-kit validation already uses P0/P1/P2 priority semantics for completion evidence, so a peck-like numeric rubric should not replace P-levels; at most it can annotate P-level decisions. Peck: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/code-reviewer.md:101`, `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/code-reviewer.md:103`; spec-kit: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/validation/validation_rules.md:351`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/validation/validation_rules.md:352`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/validation/validation_rules.md:353`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/validation/validation_rules.md:451`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/validation/validation_rules.md:452`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/validation/validation_rules.md:453`. GAP: partial. VERDICT ADAPT. EFFORT S. RISK low. BLAST-RADIUS: docs-only if optional.

### RULED_OUT
- Not net-new: read-only, findings-first review with file:line evidence already exists in both systems. Peck: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/code-reviewer.md:28`, `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/code-reviewer.md:33`; spec-kit: `.opencode/skills/sk-code-review/SKILL.md:368`, `.opencode/skills/sk-code-review/SKILL.md:370`.
- Not net-new: categorical review dimensions/security/correctness/simplicity overlap already exists. Peck: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/code-reviewer.md:70`, `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/code-reviewer.md:77`, `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/code-reviewer.md:87`; spec-kit: `.opencode/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:323`, `.opencode/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:324`, `.opencode/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:325`, `.opencode/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:327`.
- Not worth adopting literally: `score >=4 blocks` would turn minor maintainability cleanup into blocking review findings, conflicting with spec-kit P2 advisory semantics. Peck: `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/code-reviewer.md:68`, `specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/code-reviewer.md:82`; spec-kit: `.opencode/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:339`, `.opencode/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:365`.

